# ⛅ Weather App (Python + API)

A simple command-line weather application that fetches real-time weather data for any city using the OpenWeatherMap API. Great for practicing API integration, working with JSON responses, and user input.

---

## 🌐 Live Demo

👉 [Run it on Replit](https://replit.com/@smbu123/WeatherApp)

---

## ✨ Features

- 🌍 Fetches weather data by city name
- 🧠 Uses the OpenWeatherMap API to retrieve real-time weather information
- 📦 Parses JSON responses and displays:
  - Temperature
  - Weather condition
  - Humidity
  - Wind speed
- 🧪 Command-line interaction with clean prompts and output

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

- Python 3
- Requests (for API calls)
- OpenWeatherMap API

---

## 🚀 How to Run Locally

1. Clone or download this folder
2. Install the required package:
   ```bash
   pip install requests
